ve to be an extreme exception to the rule. It would also have to be with those who would not group with Ogres, Trolls, Iksar or Dark Elves for they either find dwarves/gnomes as a tasty treat or ones to whom they would enslave. Also no worshippers of evil gods..wouldnt sit well with those worshipping Brell.  It would be very family oriented with the members making a point to help those within the guild completing quests and becoming accomplished at every level. Do not misunderstand this for saying PL'ing would be encouraged...for from my experience, that seems to destroy the comraderie a guild has pretty fast for comraderie is achieved by sharing the same risks. I play a dwarven cleric in his 31st season who is also working to become a grandmaster in smithing. I dont know many who have this vision in a guild and so i post it here. Send me an email if you have the same dreams for your character.<br><br>Paul (Dhergel Forgefyre)<br>xsatyrx@yahoo.com<br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A> at: 8/19/02 3:41:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utaerinblackmaul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taerin Blackmaul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/19/02 6:46:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A guild made for those who are gnome or dwarven...</span><hr size=1> Sir Forgefyre,<br><br>Allow me a moment tae introduce meself.  Ah be Taerin Blackmaul, Rinn o House o Blackmaul.  My husband, Rik Dvalan n Ah huv a dream like yers.  Please take a moment tae join us in oor halls and visit oor fortress.  <br><br>May Brell keep ye til we meet.<br><br><br>ooc - join o